{
  "texts": [
    "Liu et al. [253] proposed a DL-based three-stage channel estimation algorithm for the IRS-aided ISAC systems.",
    "Specifically, their algorithm first decomposed the overall estimation problem into three subproblems and leveraged the CNN to successively estimate the direct links, reflected communication channels and reflected sensing channels, outperforming the traditional least-square benchmark.",
    "The aerial IRS-assisted ISAC network was investigated by Cho et al. [263], where an IRS was mounted on the UAV to establish the virtual LoS links from ISAC-BS to the users and target of interest.",
    "The CRB of target position was minimized via joint transmit beamforming, phase shift, and trajectory of UAV optimization.",
    "They developed a DRL-based algorithm to deal with the non-convex optimization problem."
  ]
}